  "original_title": "\u0d91\u0d9a\u0dca \u0db4\u0dc0\u0dd4\u0dbd\u0d9a\u0dca \u0dbd\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2 58\u0d9a\u0dca \u0dab\u0dba\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "One family owes 58 lakhs",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Professor Wasantha Athukorala of Peradeniya University's Department of Economics and Statistics told Lankadeepa on Sunday that it was found in a special study that due to the country's inflationary system, every family in the island has become debtors of 58 lakh rupees by May this year.",
        "Accordingly, he said that every person in this country has become a debtor of fifteen hundred and fifty six thousand.",
        "Meanwhile, from the year 2019 to the month of May of this year, it has been found in the same study that the borrowing of individuals from banks has increased by about 50 percent.",
        "The professor who says that the amount of debt of every family in the island has increased by about seventeen thousand and fifteen thousand rupees during that period (from 2019 to May 2022) also pointed out that the amount of debt of an individual in the island (during that period) has increased by about four hundred and sixty four thousand rupees.",
        "Furthermore, information has been revealed in that study that every person in this country will be a debtor by 526 rupees per day from the beginning of 2020.",
        "Also, Mr. Athukorala stated that due to the imposition of various types of taxes, the government increases the amount of debt of every person on the island by about 270 rupees per day.",
        "While studying all this information, he revealed that every family is becoming debtors of more than 2000 rupees per day.",
        "Thus, it has been found that every person in the island is made a debtor by the government by 1000 rupees per day and by the private loans they take, every family becomes a debtor by another thousand rupees per day."
      ],
